House Resolution 346
By: Representative Moore of the 91st
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending the National Association of Black Women in Construction;
2 and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, the National Association of Black Women in Construction (NABWIC) was
4 founded in 1991 as a national organization dedicated to increasing awareness, representation,
5 and opportunities for Black women in the construction industry; and
6 WHEREAS, the NABWIC Atlanta Chapter was officially established in 2020 to advance the
7 national mission in Georgia, providing professional development, mentorship, and advocacy
8 for Black women in construction; and
9 WHEREAS, NABWIC actively engages in community service projects to uplift and improve
10 the lives of individuals in underserved communities, including its 2023 partnership with
11 Seaborn Elementary School to create a Zen Wellness Space for teachers, its 2024
12 collaboration with HouseProud Atlanta to provide home repair assistance to seniors and
13 veteran homeowners in Atlanta, and its 2024 participation in the African American Male
14 Wellness Agency Initiative to support health screenings and awareness campaigns for Black
15 men; and
