16 WHEREAS, the NABWIC Atlanta Chapter is dedicated to legislative advocacy, ensuring
17 that Black women in construction receive equitable opportunities, fair wages, and
18 representation in government contracting and infrastructure projects; and
19 WHEREAS, NABWIC is participating in the Legislative Brunch on February 26, 2025, at
20 the Georgia Legislative Building, featuring key speakers Representative Angela Moore and
21 Senator Emanuel Jones, to advance policy discussions for increased access to government
22 contracts for Black women-owned construction firms, expanded workforce development and
23 training programs at HBCUs and trade schools, financial support for women-owned
24 businesses including grant opportunities and low-interest loans, supplier diversity and
25 procurement opportunities to ensure equitable access to large-scale projects, and safe and
26 inclusive work environments by eliminating discrimination and harassment in construction;
27 and
28 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that this outstanding organization be
29 appropriately honored.
30 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
31 the members of this body recognize and commend the National Association of Black Women
32 in Construction for its many remarkable contributions on behalf of the citizens of this state
33 as well as extend best wishes for continued success.
34 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
35 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to the
36 National Association of Black Women in Construction.
